# Frontend Deployment Guide (EC2)

This guide covers how to deploy your React/Vite frontend on the same EC2 instance.

---

## Step 1: Build the Frontend

Connect to your EC2 and run these commands:

```bash
# Go to the frontend directory
cd ~/E-commerce-product/frontend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Build the project (This creates the 'dist' or 'build' folder)
npm run build
```

---

## Step 2: Configure Nginx to serve Frontend

You have two choices:
1. **Option A**: Serve Frontend on the Main Domain (`ajxlubricant.co.in`)
2. **Option B**: Serve Frontend on a Subdomain (`listing.ajxlubricant.co.in`)

### Nginx Configuration Code:
Edit your Nginx file: `sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default`

Add this block (or update the existing one):

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name your_frontend_domain.com; # Change this to your domain

    root /home/ubuntu/E-commerce-product/frontend/dist; # Path to your build folder
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html; # Essential for React Routing
    }
}
```

---

## Step 3: Deployment Checklist

1.  **Permissions**: Make sure Nginx can read the folder:
    ```bash
    chmod -R 755 /home/ubuntu/E-commerce-product/frontend/dist
    ```
2.  **Restart Nginx**:
    ```bash
    sudo systemctl restart nginx
    ```
3.  **SSL**: Run Certbot for the frontend domain as well:
    ```bash
    sudo certbot --nginx -d your_frontend_domain.com
    ```

---

## Important Tip for API Calls
Make sure your Frontend's `.env` or API config points to your new backend URL:
`https://valisting.ajxlubricant.co.in/api`
(Otherwise, it will try to connect to localhost and fail).
